**What did you do?**
Prometheus' PV ran out of disk. Since expanding the volume it has not been able to compact and has caused the WAL to grown significantly. 

**What did you expect to see?**
Compaction succeed.

**What did you see instead? Under which circumstances?**
```
level=info ts=2020-08-05T19:53:11.276Z caller=compact.go:495 component=tsdb msg="write block" mint=1596196800000 maxt=1596204000000 ulid=01EF02VSNNYSFMVJMD6ANFZNBE duration=1m30.807383762s
level=info ts=2020-08-05T19:53:27.859Z caller=head.go:792 component=tsdb msg="Head GC completed" duration=4.785877467s
level=error ts=2020-08-05T19:53:27.859Z caller=db.go:675 component=tsdb msg="compaction failed" err="reload blocks: head truncate failed: truncate chunks.HeadReadWriter: maxt of the files are not set"
```

**Environment**

* System information:

`Linux 4.14.177-139.254.amzn2.x86_64 x86_64`

* Prometheus version:

```
/bin $ prometheus --version

  go version:       go1.14.6
```
